Holding Sovereign Debt with No Capital Is Risky, IASB Chief Says

-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 
2011-10-03T14:24:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/holding-sovereign-debt-with-no-capital-is-risky-iasb-chief-says.html
Global capital rules which allow
banks to hold no reserves against sovereign bonds creates risk,
Hans Hoogervorst, chairman of the International Accounting
Standards said in Brussels today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Moshinsky in Brussels at 
